<doc id="481562" wikidata="Q409832" url="?curid=481562" title="U.S. Route 52">
<text>U.S. Route 52 (US 52) is a major U.S. Highway in the Central United States that extends from the northern to southeastern region of the United States. Contrary to most other even-numbered U.S. Highways, US 52 primarily follows a northwest–southeast route, and it is signed north–south or east–west depending on the local orientation of the route. The highway&#x27;s northwestern terminus is in Portal, North Dakota, at the Canadian border, where it continues as Saskatchewan Highway 39. Its southeastern terminus is in Charleston, South Carolina, at Number 2 Meeting Street and White Point Garden along the Charleston Harbor.

== Route description ==
|ND
|-
|MN
|-
|IA
|-
|IL
|-
|IN
|-
|OH
|-
|WV/KY
|-
|VA
